frameDefinitions: An Agent (or inanimate Cause) affects a Set so that the number of entities that make up the Set changes from an Initial_number to a Final_number.
A Cognizer would engage in an Activity if asked or otherwise prompted to do so.
A Speaker either agrees to or refuses to engage in a Proposed_action, proposed by an Interlocutor. '' 'They agreed to express their outrage with editorials in today's paper.'
An Entity has a Temperature characterized by the target.
Due to internal forces/properties, an Entity is inclined towards a particular Behavior, which may be to perform an action or to maintain a state.
A Cognizer makes a Decision, which may be about an entity or a course of action.
frameExamples: More and more resources have been devoted to halting rogue nation's <t>proliferation</t> of controlled nuclear technology.
The court is <t>willing</t> to depart from the usual range of sentencing .
They <t>agreed</t> to express their outrage with editorials in today's paper.
The pan is already too <t>hot</t> to touch.
listRoleDefinitions: The person who causes the <fen>Set</fen> to increase in number.
The scale along which the <fen>Set</fen> ranges in, i.e., number.
The entity whose amount is being changed.
The force that causes the change.
When the proliferating occurs.
The location where the <fen>Agent</fen> changes the number of the <fen>Set</fen>.
The <fen>Cognizer</fen> is the individual that is willing to engage in the <fen>Activity</fen>.
The <fen>Activity</fen> is what the <fen>Cognizer</fen> would do under certain circumstances.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Cognizer</fen> is willing to engage in the <fen>Activity</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the <fen>Cognizer</fen> is willing to engage in the <fen>Activity</fen>.
The <fen>Speaker</fen> is the person to whom a particular action has been proposed and who responds to the request or offer made.
This is the person who proposed the <fen>Proposed_action</fen>  to the <fen>Speaker</fen> and to whom the <fen>Speaker</fen> communicates  their response.
The <fen>Proposed_action</fen> is an action that the <fen>Speaker</fen> would perform if they were to accept or refuse the request or offer.
The time interval during which the <fen>Speaker</fen> makes their verbal response concerning the proposed action.
The location in which the <fen>Speaker</fen>  gives their verbal response to the proposed action.
The <fen>Entity</fen> for which the temperature <fen>Attribute</fen> is under consideration.
The feature of an <fen>Entity</fen> which is under discussion.
A quantity or other characterization of the <fen>Entity</fen>'s state with respect to the temperature <fen>Attribute</fen>.
A modifier expressing  the deviation of the <fen>Temperature</fen> from the norm.
The <fen>Time</fen> during which the <fen>Entity</fen> is in the state of having  a particular <fen>Degree</fen> for the temperature <fen>Attribute</fen>.
TheFrame Element <fen>Entity</fen> identifies the person or thing that has a tendency towards some Behaviour.
The role <fen>Behavior</fen> marks expressions that indicate which state or action the <fen>Entity</fen> tends towards.
The <fen>Cognizer</fen> decides on a course of action.
<fen>Decision</fen> identifies the entity or course of action upon which the <fen>Cognizer</fen> decides.
The time or time period over which the <fen>Cognizer</fen> makes the decision.
The place where the <fen>Cognizer</fen> makes the decision.
listRoleExamples: <fex>My mom</fex> is very loath to take any drugs without medical supervision.
Does biology really matter more than a willingness <fex>to take an active role in a child's life</fex>?
The skillet had a temperature <fex>of 230 F</fex>
<fex>Lubomir</fex> was not inclined to believe me
Martha has a tendency <fex>to overdo the housekeeping</fex>.
The State Cabinet <fex>today</fex> decided to file an appeal in the Supreme Court seeking an extension of six months for implementation of its judgment
<fex>At the first</fex> crossroad we decided to wait.
